==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incomprehensibility
<hw>In*com`pre*hen`si*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>incompr⟦eacute⟧hensibilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The quality of being incomprehensible, or beyond the reach of human
intellect; incomprehensibleness; inconceivability;
inexplicability.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The constant, universal sense of all antiquity unanimously
confessing an <qex>incomprehensibility</qex> in many of the articles of
the Christian faith.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incomprehensible</ent>⟦br⟧
